A fellow named William Purkey once said that we should “dance like nobody’s watching”. In RECITAL, we’ll be taking taking his sage advice to the next level.

A duo of dancers will delight us with an original choreographed piece, after which a duo of improvisers will take the stage and use that dance as inspiration for one long scene. Featuring incredible artists from Chicago’s vibrant dance community and a mess of fabulous improvisers, this is one recital that will surely be a treat to attend.

With improv sets from --
Sophie Scanlon and Emma Smith
